Making news today...

* "Leading governments of Europe, mounting a new campaign to push Paul D. Wolfowitz from his job as World Bank
president, signaled Monday that they were willing to let the United States choose the bank's next chief, but only if
Mr. Wolfowitz stepped down soon." (New York Times)

* "BUNGLING George Bush made one of his great verbal blunders yesterday - as he welcomed the Queen. He said Her Majesty
had joined in America's bicentennial celebrations of 1776 - before quickly correcting himself and saying 1976. As a
crowd of 7,000 guests at the President's "gaff" laughed, Mr Bush WINKED at the Queen." (The Sun)

http://img.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2007/04_03/BushDM0507_468x308.jpg

"The Queen received the wink with a frosty glare" (Daily Mail caption to this photo:
http://img.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2007/04_03/queenbushG0705_468x306.jpg)

